an%20area%20of%20land%20and%20sea%20between%20Russia%20and%20Canada%20and%20Alaska.%20Now%20it's%20covered%20in%20water%2C%20but%20there%20was%20once%20a%20land%20bridge%20connecting%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20site%20in%20Alaska%20with%20the%20oldest%20evidence%20of%20human%20habitation%20is%20Swan%20Point%2C%20in%20the%20state's%20eastern-central%20region.%20In%20addition%20to%20tools%20and%20hearths%20dating%20back%2014%2C000%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsinkhole-south-dakota-mammoth-fossils-discovered-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emammoth%20bones%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20found%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uaf.edu%2Fnews%2Fwoolly-mammoth-movements-tied-to-earliest-alaska-hunting-camps.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethink%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20area%20was%20a%20kind%20of%20seasonal%20hunting%20camp.%20As%20mammoths%20returned%20during%20certain%20times%20of%20the%20years%2C%20humans%20would%20track%20them%20and%20kill%20them%2C%20providing%20plentiful%20food%20for%20the%20hunter-gatherers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Alaska%20may%20have%20a%20wealth%20of%20archaeological%20evidence%20of%20early%20Americans%2C%20it's%20also%20a%20difficult%20place%20to%20excavate.%20%26quot%3BYour%20digging%20season%20is%20very%20narrow%2C%20and%20it's%20expensive%2C%26quot%3B%20Feder%20said.%20Some%20require%20a%20helicopter%20to%20reach%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBlackwater%20Draw%2C%20New%20Mexico%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225550%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20crouches%20among%20big%20mammoth%20bones%20in%20a%20sandy%20terrain%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681e7abec6ad288d1480979b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224471%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20palaeontologist%20excavating%20a%20mammoth%20in%20Portales%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20circa%201960.%3Cp%3EDick%20Kent%2FFPG%2FArchive%20Photos%2FGetty%20I