tually%2C%20I'd%20catch%20up%20until%20I%20didn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221773e5b5-e787-4cae-94fc-cef9da873f3e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECredit%20card%20debt%20knocked%20on%20my%20door%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20ashamed%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20because%20I%20was%20in%20debt%2C%20but%20because%20I%20should%20have%20known%20better.%20I%20was%20taught%20early%20on%20about%20the%20power%20of%20saving.%20I%20had%20the%20privilege%20of%20financial%20literacy%20that%20most%20people%20miss%20out%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinancial%20literacy%20wasn't%20enough%20to%20prevent%20and%20predict%20my%20poor%20money%20behaviors%3B%20it%20had%20to%20do%20with%20something%20other%20than%20just%20literacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20had%20ever%20told%20me%20what%20to%20do%20when%20the%20desire%20to%20belong%20overpowers%20your%20financial%20logic.%20No%20one%20told%20me%20how%20easy%20it%20is%20to%20swipe%20a%20card%20when%20you're%20trying%20to%20build%20what%20could%20be%20your%20professional%20identity.%20I%20knew%20the%20tools%20and%20the%20concepts%2C%20but%20I%20hadn't%20learned%20how%20to%20handle%20the%20emotional%20pressure%20that%20can%20come%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdealing-with-expectations-of-succcess-in-family-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esocial%20expectations.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20started%20looking%20inward.%20Slowly%2C%20I%20began%20to%20change%20my%20relationship%20with%20money%20and%20became%20aware%20of%20money's%20emotional%20and%20psychological%20aspects.%20I%20stopped%20saying%20%26quot%3Byes%26quot%3B%20to%20everything%20and%20started%20to%20become%20interested%20in%20why%20I%20would%20say%20%26quot%3Byes%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20emotional%20roots%20of%20my%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20I%20think%20about%20money%20differently.%20Financial%20literacy%20gave%20me%20the%20foundation%2C%20but%20learning%20to%20navigate%20the%20emotional%20side%20of%20money%20truly%20ch